snippet.textDisplay:
This Virus isn't shutting down social life only in the U.S. but everywhere where the people are still sane and calm and listening to the scientists. Even here in slow reacting Germany, the public is meant to stay at home, the cases in Spain, Italy and elsewhere are rising sky-high without a real sight of an end, over 20.000 cases and more than 1000 deaths only in Spain! Italy has been hit even worse! And we haven't even reached the summit yet!



The real problem:
Irresponsible Fuckwits who buy medical devices in container loads (not exaggerated!) in order to "be prepared" without considering that this will soon leave hospitals and doctors dry. Others are still going out to Cinemas, Bars, Restaurants (if opened) and even to playgrounds (anyway prohibited as those areas are for kids and not for grown-up idiots) to party!!?!?? Please what?!? And the most disgusting thing: Many of those who should know better, well-educated people, especially students from universities and colleges and so on are saying shit like "Ah, we don't think this virus is a real threat to us, we are young and healthy, so why shouldn't we party? We are bored, we have nothing better to do right now!" They call those events "Corona Party". Such people should be locked away at least for the time being, maybe some of those should even get their scholarship taken away. They are dangerous for everyone and especially for elderly people so they need to feel the consequences for their misbehavior! They don't want to know about and/or they really do not care about the possible consequences, especially for the people surrounding them. So just make them feel them!
This has to be dealt with by lawmakers all over the world, there must be severe punishments for those who endanger people due to their own, lower motives, for those who try to gain an advantage out of the misery of the sick or their relatives, for those who are hiding medical equipment like facemasks, gloves, protective suits, etc. to make a lucrative deal when these goods are no longer available in a situation like we are experiencing right now! The existing possibilities are not making any difference whatsoever.


This Virus isn't the end of the world, not even nearly, but it shows us one thing very clearly: If there is a real danger coming upon us, we are on our own, we can't count on the responsibility of our political leaders. WE have to take action, WE have to take precautionary measures, WE have to think twice. The politicians can decide whatever they want, close borders, stop flying, traveling and everything but if WE are not willing to protect ourselves, the loved ones beneath us, the neighbors, the policemen, the doctors and nurses in our hospitals, well, if we are in need afterward, they won't be able to help us anymore because we, with our irresponsible behavior, have made it impossible for them.


Who am I to ask a doctor to treat me if he can't even protect himself because the people bought all the protective wear?


People are panicking, completely emptying the shelves at the stores without taking a minute to THINK. Most people are clueless, brainless, irresponsible idiots, sheep, endangering all of us.


STAY AT HOME! ONLY GO TO A DOCTOR IF YOU REALLY NEED TO! STOP EMPTYING THE SHELVES AT THE GROCERIES! WASH YOUR HANDS THOROUGHLY, DON'T TOUCH YOUR FACE THAT OFTEN!


AND STAY AT HOME!


Stay safe and sound everyone!


BTW.: I know it may be a bit too early (or too late? don't know) and definitely not the most important thing right now but wouldn't it be reasonable to postpone not only the shows in the first half of this year around the world but all?
I mean I was desperately looking out for some tickets for the shows in Frankfurt or Amsterdam (both sold out...SHIAT!) but with Covid-19 (or Corona - whatever you "like" the most) traveling around the world faster than we can count to 1 I think it would be safer for everyone to postpone the shows for a year.
I know it would be shitty for everyone who already got their tickets but these tickets could still be valid for the next year's shows. But that's all unimportant in the end right now.

snippet.textDisplay:
I think the planet / more developed countries like USA, Canada and other locations, people are working from home more and more. aka telecommuting.
we are in 2020 heading towards 2021, and the amount of technology we have today, more and more people are working from home, and its going to be the way the world will go.
There has been talks within the government to get rid of the paper currency and transform it into digital currency. For Example, like the Multipass in the 5th element.
And look how over 680 financial companies have brought their industry into the digital payment system with cell phones, where a person can go to a store and wave their phone to pay for things.
The reason for the government trying to get rid of coins and paper currency is, because they can transfer viruses from them. A virus can sit dormant on a paper bill for around 2 weeks.
Do you know how many hands does the paper currency transfers hands in one day ??
with thew massive amounts of AI and Automation that are taking lots of jobs, most people have internet and a computer.
So people find ways to work from home. This epidemic though really bad situation, it actually showing us what we as humans are capable of.
Think about it for a second............. many are already working from home, many corporations and companies are asking if not also demanding that people work from home.
and we as humans are proving that working from home IS POSSIBLE..... Its where humanity & technology is heading.
BTW - we are also testing the constraints and limitation of the internet backbone. Even though we currently not realizing that right now,
But we actually are, with so many people staying at home, and many are constantly on the internet. The people in charge of the internet backbone can ACTUALLY see
how much the internet itself is getting stressed, and what is needed to strengthen it if need be. We have the technology. And its 2020.... we are in the future.
